5:
Ah, more children play in the streets
these days. How wonderful.
8:
You never sound this happy. You
wanna hang up your sword to start
a nursery?
11:
Perish the thought. I'm afraid my
teaching methods would be too
strict for mere babes.
13:
Besides, I mustn't stray from my
path.
18:
As sure as the sun shines and the
winds blow.
27:
What's the matter, Lord Fang? Your
fur is disheveled.
30:
Whoa, you two seem to be awfully
friendly with each other.
35:
Whatever you're implying, it can
wait!
38:
There's a mass of angry rebels at
our gates, formed of your former
troops who are still loyal to the king!
They won't listen to a word we say!
43: What would you have me do?
47:
I wish there were another way, but
I'm afraid we can't let them continue
unabated... Lord Zahn. I leave it in
your capable paws.
55: What are you going to do?
57:
Well, he made a request, not a royal
decree. Which means I have
discretion in how I handle this
situation.
58:
Watch and learn, Lord Nimbus. This
loathsome knight you saved that
day has learned where best to
throw his life.
63: That was a perfectly good gate!
67:
Was it truly? It fell to a single swipe
of my flaming sword. I recommend
the next gate be made of reinforced
steel.
72:
Hah! He's found his funny bone! I
thought you were all about blood
and guts and death!
75:
I admit I have a penchant for
violence, or else I would've given up
the sword long ago... Now, we fight,
my brothers-in-arms.
78:
Lord Zahn! You've returned to lead
us!
80:
W-wait! Isn't that Albert by your
side? What is going on?!
82:
Allow me to ask you instead: will you
draw your swords and face me? Or
will you drop them and kneel before
him?
84:
We are soldiers loyal to the crown.
We don't brandish our blades unless
the king decrees we do. So on
whose authority do you knaves fight
now?
87:
We, we fight to avenge our king! To
protect him from those traitors who
stole the kingdom!
89:
Then you are foolish to point your
swords at Albert. If you wish to
reclaim this country, then you
should do so through political
acumen.
92:
What hogwash is this! Did you trade
your loyalty for money, Lord Zahn?!
94:
Believe whatever you'd like. I'll
entertain this tedium no longer.
98:
I am Rolf Zahn, bloody sword of the
king... If you stand in my way, then
you will taste my steel!
101:
Lord Zahn... Lord Zahn is a traitor! Kill
him! Kill them all!
104:
What? You think I'll fall to numbers
alone? You would need quite the
explosive force to even scratch me.
106:
Come at me with everything you've
got. Take my life and claim your
glory!
110:
Victory... Victory for our cause. The
sword is but a compass that points
to our true loyalties.
116:
Holy mother of... He took out all
those troops on his own.
121:
Lord Zahn is a fearsome one... I'm
glad he's on our side.
123:
Treacherous snake! Only the rightful
king deserves this victory!
125:
You will shut up, surrender, and
receive medical attention. Do not
shame your king any further.
129:
Why! If only you'd been there to lead
us...
131:
Albert has been entrusted with the
rights to govern this land. Our king's
land. To forget that is to disgrace His
Majesty's legacy.
133:
By forcing a doomed rebellion, you
risk sullying the king's name in the
annuls of history. True loyalty
requires more than blind obedience.
134:
You must protect his honor, perhaps
more so than his person. THAT is
how you display your pride as his
soldiers.
136:
Now, will you be blind hounds? Or
loyal wolves?
139:
Forgive us, Lord Zahn! We will
protect the king's honor, the king's
history! For as long as we live!
142:
Good. We will make good use of
your devotion, so that even His
Majesty learns of your deeds.
146:
Thank goodness. I was right to leave
this matter in your hands.
150:
Hah, you sure about that? But, uh,
now that I think about it...
153:
I guess teaching your sad pack of
hounds about the true meaning of
loyalty ain't such a bad thing.
